I"Í<p>Home Assistant has <a href="/docs/ecosystem/ios/">a companion app for both Android and iOS</a>.</p>
<p>As an alternative to the iOS and Android companion apps, you can add the Home Assistant â€œweb appâ€ to your homescreen as if it was native (Home Assistant leverages the W3C <a href="https://w3c.github.io/manifest/">manifest.json</a> support).</p>
<h3>Android</h3>
<ol>
<li>Open Chrome</li>
<li>Navigate to your Home Assistant instance</li>
<li>Tap on the Menu icon (three vertical bars)</li>
<li>Tap on Add to Homescreen</li>
<li>A dialog will popup; tap on Add</li>
</ol>
